verses.text:
¶ And he called \add unto him\add* the twelve, and began to
send them forth by two and two; and gave them power over unclean
spirits;

And when a convenient day was come, that Herod on his birthday
made a supper to his lords, high captains, and chief \add estates\add*
of Galilee;

And he charged them that they should tell no man: but the
more he charged them, so much the more a great deal they published
\add it\add*;

And he arose from thence, and cometh into the coasts of Judæa
by the farther side of Jordan: and the people resort unto him again;
and, as he was wont, he taught them again.

And Jesus stood still, and commanded him to be called. And
they call the blind man, saying unto him, Be of good comfort, rise;
he calleth thee.

\wj  For all \+add they\+add* did cast in of their abundance;
but she of her want did cast in all that she had, \+add even\+add*
all her living.\wj*

There were also women looking on afar off: among whom was
Mary Magdalene, and Mary the mother of James the less and of Joses,
and Salome;
